    <list type="translations">
        <item xml:lang="zh">反駁</item>
        <item xml:lang="och">難na4n</item>
    </list>
<div type="definition">
<p>PROVE that something is NOT TRUE.</p>
    </div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="old-chinese-criteria">
<p>1. There is no current and common word for refutation. The closest one can come is nàn 難 "make objections" and fēi 非 "declare to be wrong".</p>
<p>NB: Bó 駁 is post-Buddhist.</p>
        </div>
<div type="modern-chinese-criteria">
